{"word":"G4676 - σουδάριον - soudárion - soo-dar'-ee-on - Handkerchief","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">σουδάριον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">soudárion</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">soo-dar'-ee-on</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Handkerchief</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Noun Neuter / பெயர்ச்சொல் (அஃறிணை)</span>"},{"paragraph":"சீலை, கச்சை - பால் வேறுபாடற்ற பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":"a handkerchief"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>Of Latin origin; a <i>sudarium</i> (<i>sweat cloth</i>), that is, <i>towel</i> (for wiping the perspiration from the face, or binding the face of a corpse): - handerchief, napkin.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}